race.comment: PELEVECCHIO (8) has tested punters' patience but her ability is undeniable. Fifth-up now and stepping to a suitable trip, she looks perfectly placed to deliver and repay the faith. KING OF WESSEX (2) has been consistent, including a determined win here two back. Freshened with a month between runs, he just needs luck from the draw to be in the finish. AITCH D'AMICO (4) was never in the hunt last start at headquarters but is much better than that effort suggests. With the claim, he can finish strongly if the tempo is genuine. ALAINGE (6) is another who will relish a solid tempo and is one to watch if close enough turning for home.
